#DStv403​ #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - Parliament failed to conduct proper oversight over State-Owned Enterprises, according to former Public Enterprises Portfolio Committee Chairperson, Zukiswa Rantho. Rantho was testifying at the State Capture Inquiry on Tuesday. READ: WATCH: State capture inquiry hears testimony on Parliament's oversight role She says the committee only looked into allegations of corruption when the evidence was overwhelming. "I agree that the committee did not do diligence in its work because it never made any follow-up on allegations we heard," says Rantho.  Parliament failed to conduct proper oversight over State-Owned Enterprises. Former Public Enterprises Portfolio Committee Chairperson, Zukiswa Rantho, made that admission at the State Capture Inquiry. #eNCA​ #DStv403 Rantho also revealed she received threats and was intimidated for pushing through with a probe into Eskom. She says there were members of the governing party who were against the inquiry. Watch the videos above for more details on this story.